New Records: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander set a career high with seven assists in the first quarter.
Key Match Events: Jalen Williams led the team with 23 points.
Chet Holmgren added 14 points, nine rebounds, and two blocks.
Isaiah Joe hit three three-pointers on three straight possessions at the end of the third quarter to put the game out of reach for Orlando.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Oklahoma City Thunder remains the only undefeated team in the Western Conference.
Orlando Magic struggled offensively, connecting on just 35.4% of their shots.
The Magic are missing key starters Paolo Banchero and Wendell Carter Jr. due to injuries.
Oklahoma City has not won by less than 10 points all season.
